 Clean Energy Technology 


American DG Energy offers a variety of clean energy technologies, including combined heat and power (CHP), also known as cogeneration, chillers, heat pumps and boilers to provide energy costs savings along with environmental and economic benefits to our customers, all without any impact on your capital budget. American DG Energy has been recognized by the US Environmental Protection Agency for its carbon reduction efforts. These carbon offsets can earn carbon credits, which are monetized in some markets. 
Our key benefits consist of:

Lower energy costs
Capital avoidance
No responsibility
Green energy

Research indicates that customers prefer businesses that don’t just “talk green,” but show real commitment to environmental sustainability in their daily operations. This increasingly sophisticated and demanding marketplace dictates that property owners and managers find effective and efficient energy solutions to stay competitive not only on their balance sheets, but also in the minds of their customers.  
Combined heat and power (CHP)
The highly efficient combined heat and power (CHP), also called cogeneration systems deployed by American DG Energy will significantly lower your electric and hot water costs by $10,000s to $100,000s and reduce your carbon emissions by nearly 50%, offsetting nearly 18,000 tons of carbon dioxide for a 300-room apartment building, hotel, or healthcare facility (approximately 250 KW) over the course of our typical agreement.  This is the equivalent to removing 3,438 vehicles from the roadways.
Natural-Gas Cooling
Our chillers are highly efficient and can help reduce demand on the grid.  And can help your business shrink its carbon footprint. Plus, natural-gas on-site cooling keeps your building safe from summer blackouts and maintains uninterrupted comfort even on the hottest days.  Don’t have natural gas?  Or prefer an electric chiller?  We can help as we only utilize the most efficient chiller system for your individual needs.
High-efficiency hot water heaters / heat pump
Ideal for commercial and industrial sites with substantial hot water requirements, our hot water heaters are highly efficient.  Our heat pumps are twice as efficient as conventional gas-fired boilers and produce significantly fewer emissions. Water-heating efficiency is especially important, because it is the second largest use of energy in most buildings, after space heat.
Contact us today for a free site assessment.
  













